@subsubsection Brep-intersect

@b{Description}

This primitive takes two brep objects and attempts
to intersect the faces of the one with the faces of the other, yielding a 
sequence of edges which also behave as curves.

@noindent @b{Required-input-slots}

@b{:brep}

@itemize {}

 @item Object of type brep. The first brep for intersecting its faces.

@end itemize

@b{:other-brep}

@itemize {}

 @item Object of type brep. The other brep for intersecting faces.

@end itemize

@noindent @b{Optional-input-slots}

@b{:angle-tolerance}

@itemize {}

 @item Number. Defaults to (radians-to-degrees *angle-tolerance-radians-default*).

@end itemize

@b{:approximation-tolerance}

@itemize {}

 @item Number. Defaults to the max of the adaptive-tolerance of any of 
the input breps.

@end itemize

@b{:hide-edges?}

@itemize {}

 @item Boolean. Should edges be children or hidden-children? 
Defaults to nil which makes them display as children.

@end itemize

@b{:hide-points?}

@itemize {}

 @item Boolean. Should points be children or hidden-children? 
Defaults to nil which makes them display as children.

@end itemize











